The paper proposes a new programming language for web development, which suggests it belongs to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The language is designed to support modular and distributed programming, which could also fit into the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. The paper also discusses the type system, semantics, and compilation scheme of the language, which could be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
